# {{TARGET_NAME}}

Standalone Next.js 16 project extracted from VPK-Rovo's `/{{ROUTE_NAME}}` route
using the `/vpk-build` skill. Deploys to Atlassian Micros.

## Provenance

Extracted on `{{GENERATED_DATE}}` from VPK-Rovo SHA `{{SOURCE_SHA}}`. To sync
with upstream changes, re-run `/vpk-build /{{ROUTE_NAME}}` in VPK-Rovo.

## Dev

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm dev           # http://localhost:3000
```

## Build

```bash
pnpm build         # produces ./out/ (static export)
```

## Deploy to Micros

First time:

```bash
# Run the /vpk-deploy skill inside this directory.
# It will prompt for a service name and Docker credentials,
# set env vars on Micros, and run the initial deploy.
```

Subsequent deploys:

```bash
pnpm run deploy:micros
```

## Structure

- `app/` — the extracted route, promoted to the root (so `/{{ROUTE_NAME}}`
  becomes `/` in the extracted app).
- `components/` — the subset of VPK components the route transitively imports.
- `backend/` — minimal Express wrapper that serves the Next static export at
  `:8080` in production. Not used during `pnpm dev`.

## Adding to this project

Because this is a pure static export, API routes are not available. For
frontend-only features, add them normally. For features needing a backend,
either extend `backend/server.js` with new routes, or deploy the parent
VPK-Rovo instead.
